{"name":"Blind","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A blinded creature loses the ability to see. While blind they add 2 terrible die to all attack, spellcasting, and Dexterity saving throws. They cannot make reactions.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"97NHxTGVKQs0YUVW"}
{"name":"Burn","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A burning creature takes a wound die in fire damage at the end of their turn for every level of burn. On their turn a creature can spend 5 AP putting out the fire, leaving them prone. Burn ends after 1 minute or after the creature is doused in water.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"ZTfyAvKWtB22EXj5"}
{"name":"Dazed","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A dazed creature cannot take the Sprint or Reaction actions and grant combat advantage to attackers.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"8XunrYdtaCWoxowt"}
{"name":"Fear","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>a feared creature cannot willingly move closer to the source of the fear. While the source is within line of sight, they add 1 bad die to any rolls made.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"2hnDlBSp1R6R3oqf"}
{"name":"Grapple","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A grappled creature cannot move or sprint, adds 2 bad dice to Dexterity saving throws, and grants combat advantage to all creatures except the grappler.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"JT8HP8I5olHuRRUD"}
{"name":"Hex","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>When making any roll, a hexed creature replaces a critical with a single success for every level of hex on the creature. For example, a creature with hex 2 will replace the first 2 critical successes they roll with a single success each.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"ma6wuvP6NqjiPlwY"}
{"name":"Incapacitated","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>An incapacitated creature takes no actions and automatically fails Strength and Dexterity saving throws. While incapacitated they grant combat advantage to adjacent attackers, and attacks and maneuvers that deal physical damage deal an extra wound die per critical success against them.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"kqvE3jWWuNHuWEDG"}
{"name":"Paralyzed","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A paralyzed creature cannot take the sprint action, adds a terrible die to all reactions, and has their maximum AP reduced by 3 for each level of Paralyze. They may still take an action that costs more than their maximum AP as long as it is the only action they take during their turn.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"jvJlGGLlkR5tyYm4"}
{"name":"Poison","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A poisoned creature adds a bad die to all attacks, saving throws, and ability checks, adding an additional bad die for every level of poison. Only the highest level poison takes effect. For example someone who has poison and poison 2 only adds 2 bad dice instead of 3.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"SOHxPsaEsu4WRxEF"}
{"name":"Prone","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>a prone creature grants combat advantage to any melee attacker. Ranged attacks against this creature add 2 bad dice to their roll.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"pL6sk9eOgb8Sz3LA"}
{"name":"Restrained","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A restrained creature cannot move or sprint and adds 2 terrible dice to Dexterity saving throws and attack rolls. They lose the effects of a shield if wearing one and grant combat advantage to attackers.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"GM3Q1a4l585dPqyE"}
{"name":"Silenced","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A silenced creature cannot speak and adds 2 terrible dice to spellcasting rolls.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"R5ykdkWIOJeitm40"}
{"name":"Sleep","type":"condition","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A sleeping creature is incapacitated for as long as they are sleeping. A sleeping creature wakes up after being hit by an attack, maneuver, or spell, another creature spends 5 AP waking them, or they hear a loud noise.</p>"},"rollTemplate":{"value":"\n      <h1>[[i.name]]</h1>\n      <p>[[i.description]]</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"CR0hQNaCRok7vJUj":3},"flags":{},"_id":"hZZksW2XNdDPRjum"}
